data.text: Maturer is occasionally used instead of more mature.

data.chText: 明白事理的；成熟的；像成人似的

before.enText: of a child or young person

data.enText: behaving in a sensible way, like an adult
Jane is very mature for her age.

before.enText: of a person, a tree, a bird or an animal

data.chText: 成熟的橡树 / 鹰 / 象

data.enText: developed over a period of time to produce a strong, rich flavour

data.chText: （礼貌或幽默的说法）成年的，不再年轻的
data.enText: used as a polite or humorous way of saying that sb is no longer young

data.chText: 成熟的；技艺精湛的；创作于晚年的
data.enText: created late in an artist's life and showing great understanding and skill

data.chText: 经过深思熟虑；经过审慎考虑
data.enText: after thinking about sth carefully and for a long time
to become fully grown or developed

data.chText: 这一品种的牛发育成熟快。
data.enText: This particular breed of cattle matures early.

data.chText: 这一领域的技术经过过去十年的发展已经相当完善。
data.enText: Technology in this field has matured considerably over the last decade.
to develop emotionally and start to behave like a sensible adult

data.chText: 经过过去这一年，他成熟了许多。
data.enText: He has matured a great deal over the past year.

data.chText: 使（技能或素质）成熟；充分发展
data.enText: to fully develop a particular skill or quality

data.chText: 她已经成长为这个国家一位最优秀的演员。
data.enText: She has matured into one of the country's finest actresses.
if wine, cheese, etc. matures or is matured , it develops over a period of time to produce a strong, rich flavour
to reach the date when it must be paid

data.chText: 以上各词均形容人年纪大、长寿。
data.enText: These words all describe sb who has lived for a long time or that usually lives for a long time.
having lived for a long time; no longer young

data.chText: 她上年纪了，明年就75岁了。
old的委婉语，指年纪较大的、上了年纪的：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) used as a polite word for ‘old’

data.chText: 她在忙着照顾两个年老的亲戚。
data.enText: She is very busy caring for two elderly relatives.

data.chText: 年迈的亲戚住在家里有时压力相当大。
data.enText: Having aged relatives to stay in your house can be quite stressful.

data.chText: 指寿命长的、长寿的、经久耐用的、持久的：
data.enText: having a long life; lasting for a long time

data.chText: 我们家每个人都特别长寿。
data.enText: Everyone in my family is exceptionally long-lived.

data.chText: 礼貌或幽默的说法，指某人已成年或不再年轻：
data.enText: used as a polite or humorous way of saying that sb is no longer young

ex.chText: 她个子很高，而且比很多同龄女孩发育成熟。
ex.enText: She is tall and more physically mature than many girls of her years.

ex.chText: 她的花园里有几棵成熟的苹果树。
ex.enText: There are several mature apple trees in her garden.

ex.chText: 人的大脑何时完全发育成熟？
ex.enText: When is the human brain fully mature?

ex.chText: 那个年轻人就他的年龄来说算是很成熟的。
ex.enText: That young man is very mature for his age.

synonyms.bx: 指人或动植物发育成熟的；通常也指小孩或年轻人在性格、情感方面趋于成熟、明白事理的。

ex.chText: 他成年后的大部分时间是在巴黎度过的。
ex.enText: He spent most of his adult life in Paris.

ex.chText: 她以成人的方式处理这个问题。
ex.enText: She dealt with this problem in an adult way.

synonyms.bx: 指人或动物生理上发育成熟的，只作定语；也指待人接物具有成年人特点的。

ex.chText: 多数美国孩子长成大人后会离家而去。
ex.enText: Most American children will leave home after they are grown-up.

ex.chText: 他穿上西装看起来成熟多了。
ex.enText: He looked so grown-up in his business suit.

synonyms.bx: 指已长成大人的，或外表举止像成年人的。

d: 成年的，长大的；像成年人的

ex.chText: 那些苹果没熟之前不要摘。
ex.enText: Don't pick those apples until they are ripe.

ex.chText: 他们决定等到时机成熟再说。
ex.enText: They decided to wait until the time was ripe.

synonyms.bx: 多指水果、蔬菜等成熟的，也可引申指时机成熟的。

data.chText: 经过深思熟虑；经过审慎考虑
data.enText: after thinking about sth carefully and for a long time

tr: cause to ripen and discharge pus

example: we age every day--what a depressing thought!

tr: cause to ripen or develop fully
develop and work out fully in one's mind
example: I need to mature my thoughts

tr: (of birds) having developed feathers or plumage
having reached full natural growth or development
fully developed or matured and ready to be eaten or used

value.def: When a child or young animal matures, it becomes an adult.

example.ex: You will learn what to expect as your child matures physically...
example.tran: 在孩子身体发育成熟时，你就知道会发生什么事了。

example.ex: The eggs hatched and the chicks matured.

example.tran: 尚未发育成熟的小女孩

value.def: When something matures, it reaches a state of complete development.

example.ex: When the trees matured they were cut in certain areas...
example.tran: 在有些地方，树木长成后就会被砍掉。
他们的歌曲创作水平已经成熟。

value.def: If someone matures, they become more fully developed in their personality and emotional behaviour.

example.ex: Hopefully after three years at university I will have matured...
example.tran: 希望3年大学生活之后我能变成熟。

example.ex: I thought you had matured enough not to be giggly and silly about serious art.
example.tran: 我觉得你已经长大成人，不应该再冲着严肃的艺术作品傻笑。

value.tran: (在性格、感情等方面)趋于成熟

value.def: If you describe someone as mature, you think that they are fully developed and balanced in their personality and emotional behaviour.

example.ex: They are emotionally mature and should behave responsibly...
example.tran: 他们在情感上已经成熟，应该负责任地行事。

example.ex: You and I are mature, freethinking adults.
example.tran: 你我都是明白事理、思想自由的成年人。

value.tran: (性格、感情等方面)成熟的;明白事理的

value.def: If you describe the work of an artist, writer, or musician as mature, you mean that it is thoughtful and skilful and shows that their abilities have fully developed.

example.ex: It is his most mature comedy yet.
example.tran: 这是他迄今最成熟的喜剧作品。

value.tran: (画家、作家、音乐家等的技艺、能力等)成熟的，炉火纯青的

value.def: If something such as wine or cheese matures or is matured, it is left for a time to allow its full flavour or strength to develop.

example.ex: Unlike wine, brandy matures only in wood, not glass.
example.tran: 和葡萄酒不同的是，白兰地只能在木制容器而非玻璃容器里酿制。

example.ex: ...the cellars where the cheeses are matured.

example.tran: 我们最畅销的切达熟干酪

value.tran: (使)(葡萄酒、干酪等)发酵成熟;酿成

value.def: Mature cheese or wine has been left for a time to allow its full flavour or strength to develop.

example.tran: 将一些已经酿熟的切达干酪磨碎。

example.ex: ...the best place to enjoy fine, mature wines.
example.tran: 品尝葡萄佳酿的最佳之处

value.tran: (干酪、葡萄酒等)发酵成熟的，酿熟的

value.def: When an investment such as a savings policy or pension plan matures, it reaches the stage when you stop paying money and the company pays you back the money you have saved, and the interest your money has earned.

example.ex: These bonuses will be paid when your savings plan matures in ten years' time.
example.tran: 这些红利会在10年后存款到期时支付。

example.ex: ...an endowment policy that matured on September 1.
example.tran: 9月1日到期的人寿定期保险单

value.def: If you say that someone is mature or of mature years, you are saying politely that they are middle-aged or old.

example.ex: ...a man of mature years who had been in the job for longer than most of the members could remember.
example.tran: 一个已过中年的男子，大多数成员都不记得他干这行有多久了

value.tran: 成熟的;不再年轻的;老成的(婉词)

trans: 成年学生(中学毕业几年后再读大学的学生)
